import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='Date')
    plt.plot(data['Date'], data['CO2'])
    plt.title('What is the trend of CO2 concentration over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('CO2 Concentration')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['CO2'].plot(kind='hist', bins=50, color='green', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['CO2'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['CO2'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of CO2 concentration?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.scatter(data['Month'], data['CO2'], alpha=0.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('Month')
    ax.set_ylabel('CO2 Concentration')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between CO2 concentration and month?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['adjusted_CO2'] = pd.to_numeric(data['adjusted_CO2'], errors='coerce')
    plt.hist(data['adjusted_CO2'], bins=50, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['adjusted_CO2'].mean(), color='red', label='mean: {:.2f}'.format(data['adjusted_CO2'].mean()))
    plt.axvline(data['adjusted_CO2'].median(), color='blue', label='median: {:.2f}'.format(data['adjusted_CO2'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of adjusted CO2 concentration?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.boxplot([data['CO2'], data['adjusted_CO2']])
    ax.set_xticklabels(['CO2', 'adjusted_CO2'])
    ax.set_ylabel('Concentration')
    plt.title('What is the difference between CO2 concentration and adjusted CO2 concentration?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
